3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of the decoding algorithm, which is a topic relevant to distributed and parallel computing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to this sub-category if the interleaved codes are used in network communication or storage systems. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Similar to cs.SI, the paper may be relevant to this sub-category if the interleaved codes are used in network communication or storage systems.
